quran[19]{c,v,t,f}:
  83,34,"But this Day (the Day of Resurrection) those who believe will laugh at the disbelievers{1}",1:[{83:34} Narrated Anas bin Mâlik رضي الله عنه: A man said, "O Allâh’s Prophet! Will Allâh gather a disbeliever (prone) on his face on the Day of Resurrection?" He صلى الله عليه وسلم said, "Will not the One Who made him walk on his feet in this world, be able to make him walk on his face on the Day of Resurrection?" (Qatâdah, a subnarrator, said: "Yes, By the Power of Our Lord!") (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.6, Hadith No.283).]
  83,35,"On (high) thrones, looking (at all things)."
  83,36,"Are not the disbelievers paid (fully) for what they used to do?"
  87,19,"The Scriptures of Ibrâhîm (Abraham) and Mûsâ (Moses) (عليهما السلام)."
  88,16,"And rich carpets (all) spread out."
  88,17,"Do they not look at the camels, how they are created?"
  88,18,"And at the heaven, how it is raised?"
  89,13,"So your Lord poured on them different kinds of severe torment."
  89,14,"Verily, your Lord is Ever Watchful (over them)."
  89,15,"As for man, when his Lord tries him by giving him honour and bounties, then he says (in exultation): "
  90,7,"Does he think that none sees him?"
  90,8,"Have We not made for him two eyes,"
  90,9,"And a tongue and two lips?"
  91,4,"By the night as it conceals it (the sun)."
  91,5,"By the heaven and Him Who built it."
  91,6,"By the earth and Him Who spread it."
  92,1,"By the night as it envelops."
  92,2,"By the day as it appears in brightness."
  92,3,"By Him Who created male and female."